abstract: Public testimony in Congress has done little to sway Wisconsin voters' views on the possible impeachment of President Donald Trump, a new poll from the battleground state showed on Thursday.
snippet: Public testimony in Congress has done little to sway Wisconsin voters' views on the possible impeachment of President Donald Trump, a new poll from the battleground state showed on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: DETROIT — Public testimony in Congress has done little to sway Wisconsin voters' views on the possible impeachment of President Donald Trump, a new poll from the battleground state showed on Thursday.
headline_main: Poll Shows Impeachment Hearings Had Little Sway on Wisconsin Voters
headline_print_headline: Poll Shows Impeachment Hearings Had Little Sway on Wisconsin Voters

abstract: Michael Bloomberg is in “outstanding health,” but a letter from his doctor released Thursday notes that the 77-year-old Democratic presidential candidate is receiving treatment for several medical conditions, including an irregular heartbeat.
snippet: Michael Bloomberg is in “outstanding health,” but a letter from his doctor released Thursday notes that the 77-year-old Democratic presidential candidate is receiving treatment for several medical conditions, including an irregular heartbeat.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Michael Bloomberg is in “outstanding health,” but a letter from his doctor released Thursday notes that the 77-year-old Democratic presidential candidate is receiving treatment for several medical conditions, including an irregular heartbeat.
headline_main: Doctor: Democrat Bloomberg, 77, Is in 'Outstanding Health'
headline_print_headline: Doctor: Democrat Bloomberg, 77, Is in 'Outstanding Health'

abstract: Cory Booker will try to keep his presidential hopes alive by doubling down on the early voting state of Iowa, despite failing to qualify for next week's Democratic debate, his campaign said on Thursday.
snippet: Cory Booker will try to keep his presidential hopes alive by doubling down on the early voting state of Iowa, despite failing to qualify for next week's Democratic debate, his campaign said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Cory Booker will try to keep his presidential hopes alive by doubling down on the early voting state of Iowa, despite failing to qualify for next week's Democratic debate, his campaign said on Thursday.
headline_main: Democrat Booker Doubling Down in Iowa After Failing to Make Debate
headline_print_headline: Democrat Booker Doubling Down in Iowa After Failing to Make Debate

abstract: Elizabeth Warren's campaign is moving to become the first in the Democratic presidential primary to hire field staff and open field offices in Pennsylvania, early moves in a late primary state that could be an important prize if the nominee remains in doubt past March.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren's campaign is moving to become the first in the Democratic presidential primary to hire field staff and open field offices in Pennsylvania, early moves in a late primary state that could be an important prize if the nominee remain...
lead_paragraph: HARRISBURG, Pa. — Elizabeth Warren's campaign is moving to become the first in the Democratic presidential primary to hire field staff and open field offices in Pennsylvania, early moves in a late primary state that could be an important prize if the nominee remains in doubt past March.
headline_main: Elizabeth Warren Gets Campaign Effort Going in Pennsylvania
headline_print_headline: Elizabeth Warren Gets Campaign Effort Going in Pennsylvania

abstract: Ms. Warren, who has ramped up her criticism of her presidential opponents after months of avoiding conflict, issued another rebuke on Thursday in a speech about the economy and corruption.
snippet: Ms. Warren, who has ramped up her criticism of her presidential opponents after months of avoiding conflict, issued another rebuke on Thursday in a speech about the economy and corruption.
lead_paragraph: Senator Elizabeth Warren, who has ramped up her criticism of her presidential opponents after months of avoiding conflict, issued another rebuke on Thursday in New Hampshire, taking thinly veiled shots at former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and Mayor Pete Buttigieg, and calling out former Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg by name.

headline_main: Elizabeth Warren Draws Sharp Contrasts With Rivals in New Hampshire Speech
headline_print_headline: In Speech, Warren Sharpens Attacks on Rivals

abstract: Elizabeth Warren lashed out Thursday at her moderate Democratic rivals seeking the White House, accusing them of naively accepting Republican calls for unity rather than standing up to the rich while too quickly bending to the whims of their own wealthy donors.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren lashed out Thursday at her moderate Democratic rivals seeking the White House, accusing them of naively accepting Republican calls for unity rather than standing up to the rich while too quickly bending to the whims of their own w...
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — Elizabeth Warren lashed out Thursday at her moderate Democratic rivals seeking the White House, accusing them of naively accepting Republican calls for unity rather than standing up to the rich while too quickly bending to the whims of their own wealthy donors.
headline_main: Warren Slams Moderate Rivals, Laying Bare Ideological Divide
headline_print_headline: Warren Slams Moderate Rivals, Laying Bare Ideological Divide

abstract: A union in Nevada, the third state to vote in the Democratic primary, told presidential candidates that health care, specifically keeping union health care, is what’s on their members’ minds.
snippet: A union in Nevada, the third state to vote in the Democratic primary, told presidential candidates that health care, specifically keeping union health care, is what’s on their members’ minds.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — The union member had a pointed question for Elizabeth Warren: “What is your plan to make sure we keep our community health clinic?”

abstract: Can Washington do something to help them? A growing number of politicians think so.
snippet: Can Washington do something to help them? A growing number of politicians think so.
lead_paragraph: Among the millions of recent eviction cases researchers have begun to compile across the country, there are a startling number of modest sums. There are dozens of families in Texas evicted with money judgments — unpaid rent, late fees, court costs — totaling $516. There are multiple families in Cumberland County, N.C., who owed all of $301. There is a household in Providence, R.I., whose 2016 court record shows a debt of just $127.

abstract: Public opinion has shifted about impeachment, but not about the president. Here’s what that means.
snippet: Public opinion has shifted about impeachment, but not about the president. Here’s what that means.
lead_paragraph: Picture this: a president enjoying the lowest unemployment rate in decades and a booming stock market. He is about to notch a major legislative victory with the passage of a significant trade deal, has appointed two Supreme Court justices and has signed a major tax bill into law. Most voters say they’re better off financially than when he took office, according to polling this week.

abstract: Joe Biden has joined his top Democratic presidential rivals in pledging to end for-profit migrant detention centers that existed while he was vice president. He also acknowledged through his campaign the “pain” caused by deportations carried out by the Obama administration.

lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Joe Biden has joined his top Democratic presidential rivals in pledging to end for-profit migrant detention centers that existed while he was vice president. He also acknowledged through his campaign the “pain” caused by deportations carried out by the Obama administration.
headline_main: Biden Campaign Acknowledges 'Pain' of Obama-Era Deportations
headline_print_headline: Biden Campaign Acknowledges 'Pain' of Obama-Era Deportations
